# Next.js & React Patterns

## App Router
- Use the `app/` directory exclusively.
- Use `page.tsx` for route components and `layout.tsx` for shared layouts.
- Use `generateMetadata` for dynamic page SEO.
- Use `generateStaticParams` for pre-rendering dynamic routes (like case studies).

## React Server Components (RSC)
- Prefer Server Components by default.
- Only use `'use client'` for components that require:
  - Event listeners (onClick, etc.)
  - State (`useState`, `useReducer`)
  - Effects (`useEffect`)
  - Browser APIs (localStorage, etc.)

## Navigation
- Use the Next.js `<Link>` component for all internal navigation.

## Component Organization
- Place reusable UI components in `components/`.
- Keep components small and focused on a single responsibility.
